Handball has been part of my life for as long as I can remember—it’s where I grew up, not just as a player but as a person. It gave me lifetime friends, the kind you build through years of wins, losses, and shared effort. Being on the court taught me how to adapt quickly to new environments, new teams, and new challenges without losing myself. It was also my first real lesson in leadership and resilience—learning when to step up, when to support, and how to keep going even when things don’t go your way. Before anything else, handball shaped my mindset.

